Integer array of lists


// Create order array: [0, 1, 2, ..., n-1]
Integer[] ord = new Integer[n];
for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) ord[i] = i;

// Sort indices based on values in 'a' in descending order
Arrays.sort(ord, (i, j) -> Integer.compare(a[j], a[i])); // stable_sort equivalent
so Above thing is pretty good, when you have to sort the array according to indices and then indices will take 
the place according to the rank of elements in array